OL,6,FAssuming that changes do happen
OL,7,Fthere'd be implications for BBC One's
OL,8,Fdaytime schedule.
OL,10,FMorning Live at 9.15am has been
OL,11,Fsuccessful so I'd be surprised if it
OL,12,Fwas dropped. But clearly fewer
OL,13,Fprogrammes would need to be
OL,14,Fcommissioned to cover the morning
OL,15,Fschedule.
OL,17,FIs this a stealth cut or a
OL,18,Fredistribution of resources?
OL,20,FThere'd also need to be a change in
OL,21,Fafternoon commissioning.
OL,3,CChanges for BBC Breakfast and BBC
OL,4,CNews at One?
